---
import MarketingLayout from "../layouts/MarketingLayout.astro";
import { siteConfig } from "../content/site.js";
---

<MarketingLayout
  title="Terms"
  description="Closed-beta terms page for CategoryFix, written to match the current product posture and support model."
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Terms</p>
    <h1>Closed-beta terms with realistic expectations.</h1>
    <p>
      These terms are intentionally beta-oriented placeholders. They describe the current posture of
      the service and should be reviewed by counsel before broader commercial launch.
    </p>
  </section>

  <div class="legal-panel">
    <section>
      <h2>Beta service</h2>
      <p>
        CategoryFix is currently offered as a closed beta for Shopify merchants evaluating a safer
        category review workflow. Features, availability, and operating procedures may change as the
        beta evolves.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Merchant control over writes</h2>
      <p>
        The product is designed around preview before write. Merchants remain responsible for
        reviewing recommendations and deciding whether to apply category changes in their stores.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>No launch-level guarantees yet</h2>
      <p>
        The closed beta is provided for evaluation purposes. Do not rely on this placeholder page
        as a final production service-level commitment, pricing statement, or warranty document.
      </p>
      <p>No live billing is enabled in the current beta release.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Feedback and beta communication</h2>
      <p>
        Beta feedback may be used to improve the product and supporting documentation. Questions
        about access, support, or the current beta terms can be sent to{" "}
        <a href={`mailto:${siteConfig.supportEmail}`}>{siteConfig.supportEmail}</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</MarketingLayout>
